The solution iterates through the string from the last character to the first character. For each character, it creates a temporary StringBuilder to store the characters before the current character. It compares the characters and appends the current character to the temporary StringBuilder until the temporary StringBuilder has the same length as the original string or the characters match. Finally, it reverses the temporary StringBuilder and appends it to the result StringBuilder. The solution has a time complexity of O(n) because it iterates through the string once, and a space complexity of O(n) due to the StringBuilder objects used. The energy implications are low because the solution only performs a few operations on a constant amount of data.

